I'm grateful that my big bro @teampacsquad invited me on a walk today. Peace and love, family! #home 

Brooklyn, son, the rest is his

Legion and Livonia, God. 336

Who cleaned the streets with ammonia when it smelled like ****

I've been away, but homesick never felt like this 

I'd be remiss not to remind you of my actions 

And where I want the youth to be 

I'm ambitious

He said, "Times are vicious when the whole world's against us

"We told the old heads, but none of them would listen

"So, we teach ourselves, police ourselves
"We learned to do a little business

"At least I sell." 

Oh, well. Can I argue? I'm just passing back

You got a life to live, shorty. Master that

Just one more to leave on you

What I see in you reminds me of me when I was younger 

From your brown skin, your thirst and your hunger

I pray you don't fall like I did and do a number

You taught me. A broken land, if nothing else you made my heart beat

To every man, woman and child 

This is how we salute 

Heads high

'Cause you're in Brooklyn now

Heads high 

'Cause you're in Brooklyn now

Heads high

'Cause you're in Brooklyn now

This past weekend, it was my honor and privilege to return to my alma mater, Phillips Exeter Academy, to celebrate the 55th anniversary of the Afro LatinX Exonian Society (A.L.E.S.). 

Suffice it to say, my experience at the Academy would not have been what it was and what it is were it not for the existence and perseverance of the A.L.E.S. I am deeply grateful. 

It was healing to see old friends; it was inspiring to meet new ones. Thank you, @phillipsexeter. Thank you, A.L.E.S. Thank you, Prep for Prep 9. Thank you, Dr. Emery Brown '74 for lighting the way. Thank you to all in attendance for contributing to such a dynamic gathering. 🤲🏾

Photos courtesy of: Alicia Pernaw and Michelle Curtin 📷🙏🏾

It is my honor and privilege to be a guest performer at the forthcoming City Winery NYC Presents The Action Lab on December 8th at 7:30PM. I’m also thrilled to share the evening with my friend, musician, poet and activist @anatijoux

About The Action Lab: The Action Lab is a strategy center for social movements that sparks political and personal liberation. It provides rigorous and joyful spaces for organizers, leaders and artists to learn, create, and strengthen our collective capacity to win.

Tickets are available here: https://citywinery.com/new-york-city/events/the-action-lab-presents--ip95dr?utm_source=Iterable&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=nycgp112223
